page.title: 04WYKEHURST PARK BOLNEY
page.content: { Wykehurst Park}is owned by{Mr. {Golestan.}He has lived in the house for{2 years. The place has been a hotel in its time. { Baron Houte}had it built by {E.M.Barry,}whose father built the Houses of Parliament.It was built in {1860}and was finished{1874,}14 years after. There are{40}rooms in the house. On the{2nd}floor there are{10 flats which have been sold off. Single people and a couple live in them. There are{17}acres of land. { Mr.Doyle,}a previous owner,bought the place with the hall having trees growing init.It had been vandalised and it had cows living in it too.Mr. Doyle re-designed the house before selling it.
